{{Otheruses|[[Emperor Sujin]]'s fourth-generation descendant|[[Emperor Keikō]]'s grandson Mimorowake no Mikoto|Saeki no Ason}} {{Infobox Ancient Aristocrat | Name = Mimorowake no Ōkimi | image = | image_Size = | image_Caption = | Era = [[Kofun period]] | Birth_Date = Unknown | Death_Date = Unknown | Alternate_Names = Ōmimorowake no Mikoto, Mimorowake no Mikoto, Mimoriwake no Mikoto | Posthumous_Name = | Deity_Name = | Dharma_Name = | Burial_Place = | Titles = [[Kamitsuke Kuni no Miyatsuko]] | Allegiances = [[Emperor Keikō]] | Clan = {{ill|Kamitsuke Clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsuke Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Shimosuke Clan|ja|下毛野氏|1=Shimotsukeno clan|lt=Shimotsukeno clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimosuke Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimotsukeno clan|qq=}} | Parents = Father: {{ill|Hikosashima no Ōkimi|ja|彦狭島王|1=Hikosashima no Ōkimi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikosashima no Ōkimi|qq=}}<ref>『日本書紀』景行天皇紀</ref> | Notable_Features = }} [[File:御諸別王 Mimurowake no ookimi 日本百将伝.jpg|thumb|220px|Imaginary depiction of Mimorowake no Ōkimi by {{ill|Utagawa Kuniyoshi|ja|歌川国芳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utagawa Kuniyoshi|qq=}} from "Japan's 100 Generals."]] '''Mimorowake no Ōkimi''' (みもろわけのおおきみ{{Sfn|Mimorowake no Ōkimi (Ancient Clan)|2010}}, dates of birth and death unknown) is a member of the [[Kofun period]] imperial lineage mentioned in the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}}.
He is a third-generation descendant of {{ill|Toyokihiribiko no Mikoto|ja|豊城入彦命|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|1=Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyokihiribiko no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyokiirihiko-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, a prince of {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Sujin|qq=}}, and an ancestor of the {{ill|Kamitsuke Clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsuke Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitsukeno clan|qq=}}. The {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}} refers to him with the title of "Ōkimi" (king), while other sources use the titles "Ōmimorowake no Mikoto," "Mimorowake no Mikoto," or "Mimoriwake no Mikoto."
== Records ==
According to the 56th year of {{ill|Emperor Keikō|ja|景行天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Keikō|qq=}}'s reign in the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}}, Mimorowake no Ōkimi was ordered to govern the eastern provinces in place of his father, {{ill|Hikosashima no Ōkimi|ja|彦狭島王|1=Hikosashima no Ōkimi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikosashima no Ōkimi|qq=}}, who had died before assuming office. The text records that he ruled justly and quickly subdued rebellions among the Emishi. His descendants are noted to have settled in the eastern regions.
== Descendant Clans ==
The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|ja|新撰姓氏録|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Shōjiroku|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinsen Shōjiroku|qq=}} lists the following clans as descendants of Mimorowake no Ōkimi: * Imperial Lineage: ** Settsu Province: Korean Yatabe no Miyatsuko - Descendants of Kamitsuke no Ason. From Mimorowake no Mikoto's grandson, Gengo no Kimi, who was granted the surname Korean Yatabe no Miyatsuko. ** Izumi Province: Chinagata no Kimi - Same ancestry. From Mimorowake no Mikoto's descendants. ** Izumi Province: Kazurabe - Same ancestry. From Mimorowake no Mikoto's descendants.
== Analysis ==
In the {{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sendai Kuji Hongi|qq=}}, the "Kuni no Miyatsuko Honki" section under {{ill|Harima Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|針間鴨国造|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Harima Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}} refers to "Mihowake no Mikoto" as the father of {{ill|Ichiiwake no Mikoto|ja|市入別命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichiiwake no Mikoto|qq=}}, who was appointed governor of Harima. Some scholars suggest this is a transcription error for Mimorowake no Mikoto.<ref>[http://www.nihonjiten.com/data/263279.html Harima Kuni no Miyatsuko (Harima)] (Nihon Jiten).</ref>
